## 1. Core Philosophy

Everything flows from one insight.

A human trader who has been watching the market all day is fundamentally different from one who just woke up and looked at a chart. They know what happened at 9:45. They remember that BTC tried to break out at 11:00 and failed. They noticed that SPY has been quietly trending down since lunch. They have **context** — and context is what separates a decision from a guess.

The current system gives Claude no context. Every 30 minutes Claude wakes up with amnesia, looks at 12 numbers, and makes a call. That is not intelligence. That is a coin flip with extra steps.

The memory system changes this fundamentally. Claude stops being a new analyst every cycle and starts being an experienced trader who has been watching the market all day, all week, all month — and who remembers exactly what worked and what did not.

**Claude is not the analyst. Claude is the auditor.**

The rule engine does the analysis. Claude reviews the case file. This is what Claude is genuinely good at — finding logical contradictions, evaluating whether evidence coheres, catching what rules miss. The entire architecture is built around this distinction.

