## 6. The Market Regime Classifier

Runs at the very start of every cycle — before any symbol analysis. Pure Python, no LLM, fully deterministic.

### Five Regimes

| Regime | Conditions | Strategy Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| **TRENDING UP** | Higher highs/lows on 30-min, SMA20 > SMA50, volume increasing on up bars | Trend pullbacks high probability. Mean reversion dangerous. |
| **TRENDING DOWN** | Opposite of above | Mean reversion needs extreme oversold (RSI < 28). Most buys suppressed. |
| **RANGING** | Price bouncing between levels, SMAs converging, volume decreasing | Ideal for mean reversion. Breakout setups premature. |
| **VOLATILE** | VIX proxy elevated, BTC ATR spiking, wide swings both directions | All confidence scores reduced 20%. Position sizes halved. Some setups suppressed entirely. |
| **DEAD** | Volume extremely low, price barely moving | No trades. Zero cycles wasted on analysis. |

### Regime Duration Matters

A ranging regime stable for 4 hours is more reliable than one formed 20 minutes ago. Strategic memory learns how long regimes typically last. When a regime is "aging out" — approaching its historical average duration — that context is passed to Claude. The system knows a breakout may be imminent before the breakout happens.

