## 8. The Intraday Narrative Builder

Every cycle, before analyzing individual symbols, the system writes a one-paragraph plain-English description of what the market has been doing today. Stored in session memory. Injected into Claude's context.

Built programmatically from objective data — not generated by Claude.

**Example output:**

> *"Session opened with moderate upward momentum (+0.3% SPY first 30min). Regime has been Ranging since 10:15 ET (3h 27min). 4 setups detected today: 2 BTC Mean Reversion (1 approved at 10:15 — hit target +1.4%, 1 rejected at 12:00 — stale data), 1 SPY Trend Pullback (approved at open — currently +0.6% unrealized), 1 BTC Breakout (rejected — insufficient volume). Account currently +1.2% today. Notable: BTC has been oscillating in a 1.8% range all session — regime very stable. Volume declining consistently since 11:00 — possible breakout building."*

Claude reads this and has genuine situational awareness. Not guesses based on indicator snapshots — actual understanding of what has happened.

