## Appendix: The One Thing That Kills Retail Algo Systems

**Overfitting.**

Every setup in this system has a structural reason it works — not just "because the backtest showed it worked." The structural reasons:

- **Mean reversion:** Leverage liquidations cause overshoots in crypto. Structural, not historical.
- **Trend pullback:** Institutional accumulation at moving averages in uptrends. Structural, not historical.
- **Breakout:** Energy compression followed by directional release. Structural, not historical.

If you add a setup that does not have a structural reason — just a pattern that happened to appear in historical data — it will fail in live trading. This is the graveyard of every retail quant system.

The rule is simple: **before coding any new setup, write one sentence explaining why it works in terms of market participant behavior.** If you cannot write that sentence, the setup does not get built.

